00:10:53.519 --> 00:10:55.810
I actually didn't speak to
my mother and my two sisters

00:10:55.810 --> 00:10:57.250
for three years.

00:10:57.250 --> 00:10:58.870
Now what does that
actually mean?

00:10:58.870 --> 00:11:01.245
My mother was never going to
actually physically separate

00:11:01.245 --> 00:11:03.200
from me, so we lived
in the same house,

00:11:03.200 --> 00:11:05.510
and I didn't talk to
her for three years.

00:11:05.510 --> 00:11:07.010
So I would wake
up in the morning,

00:11:07.010 --> 00:11:08.370
mom would make me breakfast.

00:11:08.370 --> 00:11:11.810
I come down, eat breakfast,
I'd walk right out the door.

00:11:11.810 --> 00:11:13.940
And that's what life was like.

00:11:13.940 --> 00:11:15.650
My mom-- both my
parents, I would say,

00:11:15.650 --> 00:11:17.650
were naive about it, about
what is homosexuality

00:11:17.650 --> 00:11:19.620
and what to do and are
following the guidance

00:11:19.620 --> 00:11:21.980
of a state-licensed therapist.

00:11:21.980 --> 00:11:25.050
And I was the one who actually
became the police officer

00:11:25.050 --> 00:11:26.420
in my own home.

00:11:26.420 --> 00:11:29.170
When my mom started to see
that this is actually crazy,

00:11:29.170 --> 00:11:30.670
there can't be any
therapy out there

00:11:30.670 --> 00:11:32.530
that separates a
child and its mother,

00:11:32.530 --> 00:11:36.990
she would actually try and talk
to me and tell me, I love you,

00:11:36.990 --> 00:11:37.920
however you are.

00:11:37.920 --> 00:11:40.400
If you're gay or not, it's OK.

00:11:40.400 --> 00:11:42.950
And I would throw
a tantrum at her.

00:11:42.950 --> 00:11:44.269
You know, how dare you.

00:11:44.269 --> 00:11:46.560
Because I looked at her as
a cause of my homosexuality.

00:11:46.560 --> 00:11:47.934
And now she's
ruining the therapy

00:11:47.934 --> 00:11:50.130
that I think is-- if I had
to save my life in order

00:11:50.130 --> 00:11:51.560
to become straight.

00:11:51.560 --> 00:11:54.390
So as much as my
own mother tried,

00:11:54.390 --> 00:11:56.390
I was the one making sure
that she was not going

00:11:56.390 --> 00:11:59.340
to get close to me at all.

00:11:59.340 --> 00:12:02.720
So the years went on,
I became more popular.

00:12:02.720 --> 00:12:04.570
I actually now was
getting training

00:12:04.570 --> 00:12:07.460
by my conversion therapists,
based on stereotypes

00:12:07.460 --> 00:12:08.760
of how to be a guy.

00:12:08.760 --> 00:12:11.980
I did very well at it.

00:12:11.980 --> 00:12:13.770
However, my depression grew.

00:12:13.770 --> 00:12:14.950
My grades failed.

00:12:14.950 --> 00:12:17.510
I was almost-- I was pretty
much a straight-A student

00:12:17.510 --> 00:12:19.260
before my conversion
therapy, and I almost

00:12:19.260 --> 00:12:20.343
failed out of high school.

00:12:23.070 --> 00:12:28.576
And there was a period,
probably after my senior year

00:12:28.576 --> 00:12:31.330
where I contemplated my possible
suicide for about two years.

00:12:31.330 --> 00:12:32.789
Thought about when, where, how.

00:12:32.789 --> 00:12:34.580
I even shared it with
a friend, like, oh, I

00:12:34.580 --> 00:12:37.210
had this dream, just to see
what their reaction would be.

00:12:37.210 --> 00:12:38.380
And they laughed it off.

00:12:38.380 --> 00:12:39.963
No one really could
take it seriously.

00:12:39.963 --> 00:12:42.060
But it was something
that was real,

00:12:42.060 --> 00:12:45.200
because I knew I wasn't
becoming more straight.

00:12:45.200 --> 00:12:47.550
As I became more of a man,
my interest in men only grew.

00:12:47.550 --> 00:12:51.850
I knew exactly what I
wanted and what I liked.

00:12:51.850 --> 00:12:54.180
And so the years went on.

00:12:54.180 --> 00:12:56.760
I attempted to have
my first boyfriend.

00:12:56.760 --> 00:12:59.570
I told my conversion therapist
and my father every detail.

00:12:59.570 --> 00:13:02.590
And actually, my first boyfriend
disappeared and broke up

00:13:02.590 --> 00:13:03.260
with me.

00:13:03.260 --> 00:13:05.090
Not knowing why, and
I later found out

00:13:05.090 --> 00:13:07.840
that my father had met with
him and threatened him.

00:13:07.840 --> 00:13:10.780
And it was a friend
of mine growing up.

00:13:10.780 --> 00:13:13.800
When that happened, I
was just losing trust

00:13:13.800 --> 00:13:14.900
in everyone around me.

00:13:14.900 --> 00:13:16.270
I felt conspired against.

00:13:16.270 --> 00:13:17.580
I didn't trust the therapist.

00:13:17.580 --> 00:13:19.400
I found that he was lying to me.

00:13:19.400 --> 00:13:22.450
My own mother and sisters
knew why my boyfriend had

00:13:22.450 --> 00:13:24.200
disappeared, but I
wasn't talking to them,

00:13:24.200 --> 00:13:26.390
so it's not like they were
going to tell me anyway.

00:13:26.390 --> 00:13:27.910
And I moved.

00:13:27.910 --> 00:13:30.660
I moved to Los Angeles
to get away from it all.

00:13:30.660 --> 00:13:33.620
And for the next couple
years, I was in and out

00:13:33.620 --> 00:13:36.640
of therapy, conversion therapy.

00:13:36.640 --> 00:13:39.030
And there was a pattern
that I was picking up on,

00:13:39.030 --> 00:13:41.060
which was every
conversion therapist I

00:13:41.060 --> 00:13:43.330
met had the same story.

00:13:43.330 --> 00:13:44.960
They were gay themselves.

00:13:44.960 --> 00:13:46.170
They cured themselves.

00:13:46.170 --> 00:13:47.472
And that's how they became one.

00:13:47.472 --> 00:13:48.680
So I was like, wait a second.

00:13:48.680 --> 00:13:51.250
Have I actually ever
met someone who's

00:13:51.250 --> 00:13:53.950
converted to heterosexuality?

00:13:53.950 --> 00:13:56.710
And I never met a single
person till this day.

00:13:56.710 --> 00:13:59.330
I've met men who were
in conversion therapy,

00:13:59.330 --> 00:14:01.210
married, and had children.

00:14:01.210 --> 00:14:03.600
And they say, yeah, I still
have my attractions to men.

00:14:03.600 --> 00:14:05.790
I just don't do
anything about it.

00:14:05.790 --> 00:14:08.020
And they literally
treat their attractions

00:14:08.020 --> 00:14:12.770
to other men like alcoholism.

00:14:12.770 --> 00:14:15.440
It's there, notice it,
don't do anything about it.

00:14:15.440 --> 00:14:18.240
And that's when I really
started to question everything

00:14:18.240 --> 00:14:18.880
around me.

00:14:18.880 --> 00:14:20.720
The very thing that
I believed in so much

00:14:20.720 --> 00:14:25.120
and was really
trying to make work.

00:14:25.120 --> 00:14:26.210
And I finally had enough.

00:14:26.210 --> 00:14:29.490
And at the age of 21, estranged
from my father that point,

00:14:29.490 --> 00:14:32.430
I haven't spoken to my mother
in three years nor my sisters,

00:14:32.430 --> 00:14:36.810
I left conversion therapy
and moved back to New York.

00:14:36.810 --> 00:14:38.620
I became a server
here at a restaurant

00:14:38.620 --> 00:14:41.870
in SoHo called Balthazar, and
it was a great experience.

00:14:41.870 --> 00:14:42.990
I had a boss that was gay.

00:14:42.990 --> 00:14:46.920
I had clientele who were out.

00:14:46.920 --> 00:14:48.680
You know, executives.

00:14:48.680 --> 00:14:51.150
And it was really
just inspiring to see

00:14:51.150 --> 00:14:53.920
people living their life,
successful in whatever they're

00:14:53.920 --> 00:14:54.490
doing.

00:14:54.490 --> 00:14:56.710
And whatever their
sexual orientation is

00:14:56.710 --> 00:14:58.700
had made no difference
to their life.

00:15:02.030 --> 00:15:05.580
So after that, I was able to
actually see a psychotherapist

00:15:05.580 --> 00:15:06.490
for the first time.

00:15:06.490 --> 00:15:08.448
I had actually never seen
one, an actual person

00:15:08.448 --> 00:15:09.920
who does therapy.

00:15:09.920 --> 00:15:13.990
And it's a-- [LAUGHS] and
it took a lot of trust.

00:15:13.990 --> 00:15:15.600
It was a new experience for me.

00:15:15.600 --> 00:15:17.300
I also did a program
called Landmark,

00:15:17.300 --> 00:15:19.880
which is a global personal and
professional training company.

00:15:19.880 --> 00:15:24.790
And I got so inspired
from there by mentors,

00:15:24.790 --> 00:15:26.480
and I started to
look at my own life.

00:15:26.480 --> 00:15:28.427
How my whole life I
was trying to fit in.

00:15:28.427 --> 00:15:30.260
And I noticed that the
conversion therapists

00:15:30.260 --> 00:15:33.370
who were treating me were trying
to fit in, in their own life.

00:15:33.370 --> 00:15:36.350
And my father who I hadn't
spoken to in five years

00:15:36.350 --> 00:15:38.510
was trying to be a great dad.

00:15:38.510 --> 00:15:40.420
Now I didn't believe
that for a long time.

00:15:40.420 --> 00:15:42.010
And I went and spoke to him.

00:15:42.010 --> 00:15:44.362
So it was in 2012.

00:15:44.362 --> 00:15:45.820
I hadn't seen my
dad in five years.

00:15:45.820 --> 00:15:49.230
My father moved back to
Israel where he's from.

00:15:49.230 --> 00:15:51.380
And I had a
conversation with him.

00:15:51.380 --> 00:15:55.110
And I said to my dad,
I want to see you.

00:15:55.110 --> 00:15:57.102
It's been five years.

00:15:57.102 --> 00:15:58.060
Can I come and see you?

00:15:58.060 --> 00:15:59.230
I'm going to fly to Israel.

00:15:59.230 --> 00:16:00.680
And I flew there.

00:16:00.680 --> 00:16:02.340
I was only there for three days.

00:16:02.340 --> 00:16:04.961
And I was with my
whole family there.

00:16:04.961 --> 00:16:05.710
Everyone is there.

00:16:05.710 --> 00:16:07.150
And we had dinner together.

00:16:07.150 --> 00:16:09.390
And I made a gay
joke at the table.

00:16:09.390 --> 00:16:11.280
Everyone laughs except my dad.

00:16:11.280 --> 00:16:14.080
And my dad said to me, you
know, let's take a walk.

00:16:14.080 --> 00:16:16.141
And he looked--
and he said to me--

00:16:16.141 --> 00:16:17.390
we walked away from the table.

00:16:17.390 --> 00:16:20.800
And he said to me, so, whatever
happened to your conversion

00:16:20.800 --> 00:16:21.860
therapy?

00:16:21.860 --> 00:16:22.550
Are you gay?

00:16:22.550 --> 00:16:23.050
Are you not?

00:16:23.050 --> 00:16:25.090
It sounds like
you're openly gay.

00:16:25.090 --> 00:16:27.777
And I said, yeah, dad.

00:16:27.777 --> 00:16:30.110
I've met some really great
people, some really inspiring

00:16:30.110 --> 00:16:32.400
people, and this is who I am.

00:16:32.400 --> 00:16:35.080
I am openly gay.

00:16:35.080 --> 00:16:37.760
And my dad started this
rant-- which he always says,

00:16:37.760 --> 00:16:40.519
I probably have it memorized--
how I can't be gay,

00:16:40.519 --> 00:16:42.060
I don't understand
what the world is,

00:16:42.060 --> 00:16:43.885
and I'm going to hurt myself.

00:16:43.885 --> 00:16:46.260
And my automatic reaction
would be to like fight with him

00:16:46.260 --> 00:16:49.390
verbally to stop this.

00:16:49.390 --> 00:16:50.230
But I just listen.

00:16:50.230 --> 00:16:52.537
And it was for the first
time, through all my work

00:16:52.537 --> 00:16:54.120
and all my healing,
I was able to hear

00:16:54.120 --> 00:16:56.770
how scared my father was.

00:16:56.770 --> 00:16:58.230
My dad was terrified.

00:16:58.230 --> 00:17:02.940
I'm his only son, he had no
idea what to do about this.

00:17:02.940 --> 00:17:05.910
And I stopped him after 10
minutes of him rambling on.

00:17:05.910 --> 00:17:10.024
And I said, dad, there is
nothing to worry about.

00:17:10.024 --> 00:17:12.190
Now, I've never actually
looked at my dad in the eye

00:17:12.190 --> 00:17:14.236
and said there's
nothing to worry about.

00:17:14.236 --> 00:17:16.319
I don't know if anyone
really tells their parents,

00:17:16.319 --> 00:17:18.901
guys, it's OK, mom and dad.

00:17:18.901 --> 00:17:21.109
And he looked at me, he's
like, how can you say that?

00:17:21.109 --> 00:17:22.317
How can you say not to worry?

00:17:22.317 --> 00:17:25.550
And I was, like, dad, I know
exactly what the world is.

00:17:25.550 --> 00:17:27.020
I know exactly who I am.

00:17:27.020 --> 00:17:30.660
And my promise to you is
I will take care of myself

00:17:30.660 --> 00:17:31.897
as it comes.

00:17:31.897 --> 00:17:33.480
There's really nothing
to worry about.

00:17:33.480 --> 00:17:35.930
Look around.

00:17:35.930 --> 00:17:38.320
We're here together for the
first time in five years.

00:17:38.320 --> 00:17:40.530
Is there anything
wrong happening?

00:17:40.530 --> 00:17:43.240
And my father said, OK.

00:17:43.240 --> 00:17:45.716
Now what happened in that
moment was I got my father back,

00:17:45.716 --> 00:17:47.090
and I recognized
that I was never

00:17:47.090 --> 00:17:51.370
going to-- I was never going
to sacrifice my relationship

00:17:51.370 --> 00:17:52.605
with my father ever again.

00:17:52.605 --> 00:17:53.980
Now this doesn't
mean my father's

00:17:53.980 --> 00:17:56.490
going to march on Fifth
Avenue during gay pride.

00:17:56.490 --> 00:17:58.224
That's the last thing
he's going to do.

00:17:58.224 --> 00:18:00.390
But what started, what
opened up was a conversation.

00:18:00.390 --> 00:18:02.827
And my dad is someone I
talk to almost every day.

00:18:02.827 --> 00:18:05.160
And when he has questions or
things he doesn't-- that he

00:18:05.160 --> 00:18:07.470
can't work out for himself
about me being openly gay,

00:18:07.470 --> 00:18:09.200
we talk about it.

00:18:09.200 --> 00:18:11.070
And that's just
how it looks like.

00:18:11.070 --> 00:18:13.200
And it's great.

00:18:13.200 --> 00:18:15.570
The next person I
wanted to reach out

00:18:15.570 --> 00:18:18.700
to make peace to, or start a
conversation [INAUDIBLE] what

00:18:18.700 --> 00:18:21.080
is going to happen
was one therapist

00:18:21.080 --> 00:18:23.080
who treated me for three years.

00:18:23.080 --> 00:18:26.700
And this man was
living in Los Angeles.

00:18:26.700 --> 00:18:29.380
And I didn't know what
he was going to say,

00:18:29.380 --> 00:18:30.970
so I sent an email.

00:18:30.970 --> 00:18:32.669
And said to him,
hey, I would love

00:18:32.669 --> 00:18:35.210
to share a conversation with
you and share my accomplishments

00:18:35.210 --> 00:18:36.420
since we last met.

00:18:36.420 --> 00:18:38.430
Would you be interested?

00:18:38.430 --> 00:18:40.330
He didn't answer
the email, he just

00:18:40.330 --> 00:18:41.650
called me 15 minutes later.

00:18:41.650 --> 00:18:43.620
And I had a heart attack.

00:18:43.620 --> 00:18:46.220
And I didn't pick up the call.

00:18:46.220 --> 00:18:48.340
He called again, maybe
another 30 minutes later.

00:18:48.340 --> 00:18:49.770
I'm, like, just get on the call.

00:18:49.770 --> 00:18:51.660
I started this.

00:18:51.660 --> 00:18:57.206
And it was just like,
hi, how are you?

00:18:57.206 --> 00:18:59.080
And I shared with him
all my accomplishments.

00:18:59.080 --> 00:19:00.510
I shared with him
how I came out,

00:19:00.510 --> 00:19:04.310
how I told my dad not to worry,
that life's going to be OK.

00:19:04.310 --> 00:19:07.180
And I told him that I'm
going to become a gay rights

00:19:07.180 --> 00:19:09.580
advocate, because I made a
YouTube video that just went

00:19:09.580 --> 00:19:13.363
viral, and I just got invited to
speak at Creating Change, which

00:19:13.363 --> 00:19:16.550
is a national LGBT conference.

00:19:16.550 --> 00:19:19.380
And he said, wow.

00:19:19.380 --> 00:19:21.850
He said, you know, you're
one of-- he started to share,

00:19:21.850 --> 00:19:24.970
you're one of 13 guys I
treated who I never cured.

00:19:24.970 --> 00:19:26.530
I said, OK.

00:19:26.530 --> 00:19:29.282
So does that mean you're
not practicing anymore?

00:19:29.282 --> 00:19:30.740
And he started to
share with me how

00:19:30.740 --> 00:19:32.780
he was in a really
bad place in his life.

00:19:32.780 --> 00:19:36.990
He spent all his money going
to school, getting a PhD.

00:19:36.990 --> 00:19:41.692
And the last thing he thought
he was doing was hurting people.

00:19:41.692 --> 00:19:43.400
And he says, I don't
actually really know

00:19:43.400 --> 00:19:46.090
the full damage of what I did.

00:19:46.090 --> 00:19:50.200
And he has a wife and two
kids, and people won't even

00:19:50.200 --> 00:19:51.190
hire me right now.

00:19:51.190 --> 00:19:52.935
And I don't even
know what to do.

00:19:52.935 --> 00:19:55.060
What was interesting was
the tables sort of turned.

00:19:55.060 --> 00:19:57.380
I now was the
therapist, in a way.

00:19:57.380 --> 00:19:59.810
And he was like the
patient seeking help.

00:19:59.810 --> 00:20:03.020
And I just really got
the humanity in him.

00:20:03.020 --> 00:20:07.830
And we started to talk every
week and just became friendly.

00:20:07.830 --> 00:20:11.380
And I shared with him that I
know I'm going to be speaking.

00:20:11.380 --> 00:20:12.977
I'm going to be
sharing our story.

00:20:12.977 --> 00:20:14.810
My years with you, I
really cared about you.

00:20:14.810 --> 00:20:17.020
I believe there was
some of the best time.

00:20:17.020 --> 00:20:19.520
I didn't realize the harm that
was happening to me because I

00:20:19.520 --> 00:20:20.620
believed in the therapy.

00:20:20.620 --> 00:20:22.450
And I said, do I
get your-- will I

00:20:22.450 --> 00:20:26.120
have your blessing to go speak
nationally about this issue?

00:20:26.120 --> 00:20:27.400
And he said, of course.

00:20:27.400 --> 00:20:29.600
And please tell me
everything that happens.

00:20:29.600 --> 00:20:31.020
We started to become friendlier.

00:20:31.020 --> 00:20:35.960
And as time went by, a lot
was going on in the country.

00:20:35.960 --> 00:20:38.030
Conversion therapy
became a national topic.

00:20:38.030 --> 00:20:42.570
It almost pretty much
did not exist before.

00:20:42.570 --> 00:20:44.950
And there was a big
lawsuit that started.

00:20:44.950 --> 00:20:47.230
I was invited to be a part
of against a few conversion

00:20:47.230 --> 00:20:48.850
therapists, some
that had treated me.

00:20:48.850 --> 00:20:50.300
And I declined to
be a part of it.

00:20:50.300 --> 00:20:52.590
And instead, I asked
this particular therapist

00:20:52.590 --> 00:20:54.590
if he would join
me in an interview.

00:20:54.590 --> 00:20:56.560
We get to share
our story together.

00:20:56.560 --> 00:20:59.710
Former patient,
former therapist.

00:20:59.710 --> 00:21:01.460
And we created an
article-- I believe it's

00:21:01.460 --> 00:21:04.780
the next slide-- this article.

00:21:04.780 --> 00:21:07.517
And it says, "True Colors,
Getting Over the Gay Cure."

00:21:07.517 --> 00:21:09.600
And we sat side by side--
it was the first time we

00:21:09.600 --> 00:21:12.970
saw each other in five years--
and we talked about, together,

00:21:12.970 --> 00:21:15.800
what conversion therapy
was like for both of us.

00:21:15.800 --> 00:21:18.590
And I just recognized
the impact of this versus

00:21:18.590 --> 00:21:21.490
if he was behind a bench
and I was suing him.

00:21:21.490 --> 00:21:23.915
And I was actually
standing for him.

00:21:23.915 --> 00:21:26.040
I wanted him to get the
life that he wanted to live

00:21:26.040 --> 00:21:28.050
and what he was-- why
did he go to school?

00:21:28.050 --> 00:21:29.300
Why did he become a therapist?

00:21:29.300 --> 00:21:31.510
I became interested in
what he wanted in his life.

00:21:31.510 --> 00:21:35.280
And we got to create this
incredible article together.

00:21:35.280 --> 00:21:38.840
So as time went on, I
am now a advisory member

00:21:38.840 --> 00:21:42.029
to a campaign called-- it's
a hashtag-- #BornPerfect.

00:21:42.029 --> 00:21:43.570
It was created by
the National Center

00:21:43.570 --> 00:21:45.630
for Lesbian Rights
in San Francisco.

00:21:45.630 --> 00:21:48.510
And our goal is by
2019 we will end

00:21:48.510 --> 00:21:51.020
conversion therapy nationwide.

00:21:51.020 --> 00:21:52.240
Our advocacy has continued.

00:21:52.240 --> 00:21:55.420
So far, conversion therapy has
been outlawed in six US states

00:21:55.420 --> 00:21:56.640
for minors only.

00:21:56.640 --> 00:22:00.560
And we have federal legislation
right now pending in Congress.

00:22:00.560 --> 00:22:04.230
Considering that this movement
has only started in two years,

00:22:04.230 --> 00:22:06.590
our progress has
been outstanding.

00:22:06.590 --> 00:22:09.570
And we really believe that
by 2019, conversion therapy

00:22:09.570 --> 00:22:12.632
will be outlawed.

00:22:12.632 --> 00:22:13.840
This is just another article.

00:22:13.840 --> 00:22:15.680
This is me when I--
in "Time" magazine, I

00:22:15.680 --> 00:22:17.260
wrote an op-ed for "Time."

00:22:17.260 --> 00:22:20.020
And that's when I was
speaking in Albany.

00:22:20.020 --> 00:22:22.657
I got really-- it's punked.

00:22:22.657 --> 00:22:25.240
I put my-- I don't know how my
hands got in the air like that,

00:22:25.240 --> 00:22:26.200
actually.

