00:53:00.240 --> 00:53:03.505
you wish they would know or do.

00:53:03.505 --> 00:53:06.130
MATTHEW SHURKA: So just to make
sure I understand the question.

00:53:06.130 --> 00:53:07.270
Let's say I'm a
person who did not

00:53:07.270 --> 00:53:09.290
go through conversion therapy
but I'm dating someone who has.

00:53:09.290 --> 00:53:10.010
AUDIENCE: Correct.

00:53:10.010 --> 00:53:11.759
What advice do you
have for yourself then?

00:53:14.007 --> 00:53:15.673
MATTHEW SHURKA: That's
a great question.

00:53:18.460 --> 00:53:21.750
It also depends where the
person is along their journey,

00:53:21.750 --> 00:53:24.800
because what we're seeing with
conversion-- former conversion

00:53:24.800 --> 00:53:30.890
therapy patients-- it
becomes a lifelong challenge.

00:53:30.890 --> 00:53:32.540
Especially for minors
who were in it,

00:53:32.540 --> 00:53:34.910
there's a pattern of they
keep putting themselves back

00:53:34.910 --> 00:53:36.970
into conversion therapy
because they believe

00:53:36.970 --> 00:53:38.480
they failed the therapy.

00:53:38.480 --> 00:53:39.440
I was one of them.

00:53:39.440 --> 00:53:42.960
I put my-- at 19, my mother
and father were not in my life,

00:53:42.960 --> 00:53:45.470
and I put myself back
into conversion therapy,

00:53:45.470 --> 00:53:47.370
because I didn't
try hard enough.

00:53:47.370 --> 00:53:49.650
And conversion therapists
will tell you that, too.

00:53:49.650 --> 00:53:54.040
So there is so much that they
go through, even in the years

00:53:54.040 --> 00:53:56.510
after.

00:53:56.510 --> 00:54:00.240
I guess my advice
is really listen,

00:54:00.240 --> 00:54:02.810
get where they're at,
what are they comfortable

00:54:02.810 --> 00:54:05.060
with, what are they
not comfortable with.

00:54:05.060 --> 00:54:10.755
And just so you can
be on their page.

00:54:10.755 --> 00:54:11.880
So you know where they are.

00:54:11.880 --> 00:54:14.562
You know what to expect.

00:54:14.562 --> 00:54:16.270
If they're being-- if
they're telling you

00:54:16.270 --> 00:54:17.140
that they were in
conversion therapy

00:54:17.140 --> 00:54:19.400
and they're being open
with you enough about it,

00:54:19.400 --> 00:54:21.944
and there's things that--
it sounds like-- I'm not

00:54:21.944 --> 00:54:23.860
sure exactly what the
problem is specifically,

00:54:23.860 --> 00:54:28.680
but there's a lot of--
one common thing is shame.

00:54:28.680 --> 00:54:31.712
And when I came out of the
closet, I was not proud.

00:54:31.712 --> 00:54:33.420
I came out not proud,
because I was like,

00:54:33.420 --> 00:54:34.990
what if I made a mistake?

00:54:34.990 --> 00:54:36.540
What if I want to go back
into conversion therapy?

00:54:36.540 --> 00:54:38.540
What if I still want to
try and be heterosexual?

00:54:38.540 --> 00:54:40.540
And I was out.

00:54:40.540 --> 00:54:42.690
And it took about--
it took months,

00:54:42.690 --> 00:54:44.470
and there was
specific people I met

00:54:44.470 --> 00:54:48.630
who, I got like, I'm actually
great exactly the way I am,

00:54:48.630 --> 00:54:50.260
and I can be proud of being gay.

00:54:53.310 --> 00:54:56.090
So I really-- I think if you're
in a relationship with someone

00:54:56.090 --> 00:54:58.120
who's been through
conversion therapy,

00:54:58.120 --> 00:55:01.070
really want to listen to
them, hear where they're at.

00:55:01.070 --> 00:55:02.685
And if you are
obviously willing to be

00:55:02.685 --> 00:55:05.310
in that relationship with them,
and go through whatever they're

00:55:05.310 --> 00:55:07.430
going through, just want
to love and support them

00:55:07.430 --> 00:55:08.895
wherever they are.

00:55:08.895 --> 00:55:10.770
And get to know what
your ex-- what to expect

00:55:10.770 --> 00:55:12.160
and what not to expect.

00:55:12.160 --> 00:55:14.350
And be good with it.

